The publicity sub-committee Chairman for the All Progressives Congress (APC) National Convention, Abdullahi Sule has revealed why President Muhammadu Buhari and Governors of the party opted for consensus for the election of the National Chairman. Sule, who is also the Governor of Nasarawa State revealed that Buhari and the governors made the crucial decision to have a peaceful exercise on Saturday. Daily Independent had on Wednesday reported that Buhari meet with APC governors at the statehouse, Abuja, where they agreed on consensus. Speaking at the National Secretariat in Abuja, the governor noted that the APC governors were now more united and would go into the convention as one united family. According to him, the number of delegates had not been ascertained yet, adding that the number would be determined after accreditation. He said, “As I mentioned earlier, we have been driven towards a consensus arrangement so that we can have a very peaceful convention after which most of the political activities will begin which will lead into the success of the party at most of the elections that we are going to have next year by the grace of God. “We also look forward actually to a convention that is going to signify our unity and our strength as we come together to face the election next year. So I thank you sincerely for coming. That is why we have come here to be able to discuss these issues with you.”